Introduction

The beatochess homepage is a repository of ongoing work. It contains

  • revisions (corrections, versions, modification) of and comments on studies by other authors
  • a collection of my own studies

Updates since last version

Not appicable (since this is the first version)

Legend

  • (c): correction; i.e.original study was unsound.
  • (m): modification; i.e.original study was sound, the improvement has another motivation.
  • (s): corrected solution (without changing the position).
  • (v): version (perhaps a correction or a modification).
  • BN: Beat Neuenschwander
  • AN: 100% anticipation: the whole study was published earlier by someone else.
  • CR: colours reversed (the original stipulation was: Black to win/draw).
  • MC: too many composers to fit the White field. All names given as text before the first move.
  • PH: posthumously published.
  • SSZ: Schweizerische Schachzeitung
  • TE: theoretical ending (i.e.probably not an endgame study).
  • TT: theme tourney.
  • TW: twin study (also triplicates, quadruplicates, etc).
  • U1: second solution (at move 1).
  • U2: cook; extra solution after move 1.
  • U3: incorrect; White is unable to fulfil the stipulation (in a win study Black draws or wins; in a draw study White loses).
  • U4: super-cook. White can even win in a study with a draw stipulation.
  • U5: illegal initial position.

Revised studies (corrections, etc.)

Note: in my revisions, the author will be given as Original Author BN. This is a small deviation to the HHdbVI database by Harold van der Heijden, where the author of the revision is only mentioned in the solution.
